author: STEPHEN HAWKINS
title: No. 5 Baylor running into Big 12 opener vs. Texas Tech
text:
Sports No. 5 Baylor running into Big 12 opener vs. Texas Tech FILE - In this Sept. 26, 2015, file photo, Texas Tech wide receiver Jakeem Grant (11) runs in for a touchdown after a reception in the first half of an NCAA college football game against TCU in Lubbock, Texas. Baylor, ... more > By STEPHEN HAWKINS   
ARLINGTON, Texas (AP) - Even coach Art Briles finds it a bit mind-boggling that fifth-ranked Baylor is the nation’s top rushing team. 
What comes as no real surprise is that the Bears are still the highest-scoring team with the best overall offense. 
The two-time defending Big 12 champions, who are off to a 3-0 start, play their league opener Saturday against Texas Tech at the Dallas Cowboys’ NFL stadium. 
Texas Tech is third nationally and second in the Big 12 with 54 points a game. That’s 10 less than Baylor, the national leader the past two seasons in scoring and total offense. 
The Bears are averaging nearly 380 yards rushing per game. Their 767 total yards a game are 130 more than second-best TCU, which last week won 55-52 at Texas Tech
